snippet.textDisplay: I loved Eugene and his sister. I’d be proud to have her as a little sister. They were my favorite part, mostly because it makes Eugene seem a lot more “normal” because there is someone else who is clearly very much like him. Of course I say normal for lack of a better word. I’m really happy that as much as the other Try Guys are surprised when he’s relaying things from his childhood or something in his life, he is not alone in it. I’m just glad he’s not alone. I really wish I had better words for it, but they were my favorite for sure!
